HEADWORD: Calyptra
<hw>Ca*lyp"tra</hw> <pr>(k⟦adot⟧*l⟦icr⟧p"tr⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>kaly`ptra</grk> a covering for the head, fr.
<grk>kaly`ptein</grk> to cover.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A little
hood or veil, resembling an extinguisher in form and position, covering
each of the small flasklike capsules which contain the spores of mosses;
also, any similar covering body.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Calyptriform</ent>⟦br⟧
